What did you learn about maintaining good health while on the road?

That is probably one of the hardest things for everybody on the road. You get a tummy bug or get extremely ill very quickly. It’s a very, very big issue, not just physically but mentally, as well. Fatigue becomes an issue. If you are constantly under stress and overly tired the psychological effects become more intense.

The most frustrating thing is that often your body can’t cope. You may feel you can endure the pain for two weeks but after two to three weeks, you’re ready to just give up. When I didn’t feel good, I just wanted to give up everything. That’s when it’s also more important to go back to your friends and people you’ve met on the road and ask them to look after you.

Some of the places we have been to have not been positive and there have been some really negative experiences. In Saudi Arabia, we have had so many road blocks. The first two days we spent six hours at the road blocks and they didn’t care we were cycling. They just wanted the bike threw it into the back with mattresses.
